# ~/.bashrc.secrets
#
# Local shell secrets for interactive Bash sessions. The baseline dot_bashrc
# sources this file if it exists, so anything exported here is available in
# Bash shells and commands launched from them.
#
# Safety rules:
#   - This file is owned by YOUR user. Do not commit it anywhere, even to a
#     private overlay repo.
#   - Keep shared non-secret exports in ~/.config/work/env.sh.
#   - Keep interactive-only Bash helpers in ~/.bash/work.bash.
#   - `chmod 600 ~/.bashrc.secrets` so other local users cannot read it.
#   - Rotate any token that has ever landed in a committed file.

# Examples (replace with your real values in the real overlay, never here):
#
# export GIT_HOST_TOKEN="<your-hosted-git-token>"
# export GITHUB_TOKEN="<your-github-pat>"
# export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="<your-anthropic-key>"
